[% META title = 'Hive Inspection System' %]
[% META description = 'How to record and review hive inspections in the beekeeping (Apiary) module' %]
[% META roles = 'admin developer editor' %]

<h1>Hive Inspection System</h1>
<p><em>Last updated: April 28, 2026</em></p>

<h2>Overview</h2>
<p>
The Hive Inspection module is part of the Apiary (beekeeping) controller.
It allows beekeepers to record hive inspections with observations, feeding records,
and frame-level detail. A visual hive diagram helps you see the physical state of the hive at a glance.
An inspection calendar gives a historical overview, and printable reports are available for sharing.
</p>

<hr>

